Introduction

False Profits is a share market game where players are given $1 million dollars to trade stocks listed on the Australian stock market. Players compete to become Top Trader.

This user guide is divided into two main sections; The Guides section shows you how to perform certain tasks, the Reference section identifies what is displayed on each screen.

This document is available online at https://github.com/SeamusBoyle1/falseprofits-userguide/wiki

Download False Profits

False Profits can be downloaded from the GitHub Releases page. Downloads are available for Windows 64-bit, Mac, and Android. You can get the iOS version in the App Store. You can also build from source (see Building False Profits from source section in the Development Guide).

Sign up for a new user account

  1. When you start the app for the first time, or when you have signed out of another user account the app will display the Sign in screen. Select Create an account.
  2. Enter a Name, Email, and Password.
  3. If the details you input appear valid press the Create Account button. If the button is not enabled you entered something incorrectly and will need to check the details you entered.

Sign in to an existing user account

  1. When you start the app for the first time, or when you have signed out of another user account the app will display the Sign in screen.
  2. Enter the Email and Password you previously registered.
  3. If the details you input appear valid, tap the Sign in button. If the button is not enabled you entered something incorrectly and will need to check the details you entered.
  4. If your details are correct you will be signed in on your device and the Sign in screen will close. Your device will remain signed in until you sign out, you will periodically have to re-sign in (currently around once-per-week).

Sign out from a device

To sign out you must already be signed in.

  1. Open the navigational drawer (see Navigation Drawer)
  2. Select Sign out
  3. A confirmation screen will be displayed, asking Really sign out?, select Yes to sign out or No to cancel.

View or edit my profile

  1. Open the navigational drawer (see Navigation Drawer)
  2. Select Profile
  3. If all you want to do is view your profile you are done, otherwise
  4. Change your email address and name to the new values
  5. If the details you input appear valid, select the Save Changes button. If the button is not enabled you entered something incorrectly and will need to check the details you entered. If you changed your mind and now don't want to edit your details press the Cancel button undo your changes.

Reset trading account balance

  1. Open the navigational drawer (see Navigation Drawer)
  2. Select Profile
  3. From the app bar open the overflow menu
  4. Select Reset Account
  5. A confirmation dialog is displayed, select Yes to reset your trading account or No to cancel.

Delete user account

  1. Open the navigational drawer (see Navigation Drawer)
  2. Select Profile
  3. From the app bar open the overflow menu
  4. Select Delete User
  5. A confirmation dialog is displayed, select Yes to delete your user account or No to cancel.

Look up a stock quote

  1. Open the navigational drawer (see Navigation Drawer)
  2. Select Quotes
  3. Tap the search button displayed on the app bar
  4. In the text entry field enter a search term, either the share code or part of the company name you want a quote for
  5. Press the search button
  6. The matching shares will be displayed, tap one of the search results to view a quote. If no shares match the search term you entered a No companies message will be displayed instead.

View a price chart

  1. To view a stock chart you first need to look up a quote (see Lookup a stock quote)
  2. Tap the Fullscreen button
  3. See Fullscreen chart reference page for an overview

View your watchlist

  1. Open the navigational drawer (see Navigation Drawer)
  2. Select Quotes
  3. Tap the Watchlist tab button displayed on the tab bar
  4. See Watchlist reference page for an overview

Add or remove watchlist symbols

Add or remove symbol using stars on the quotes screen

  1. To add a symbol from the quotes screen you first need to look up a quote (see Lookup a stock quote)
  2. Press the star button to add or remove the symbol from your watchlist. The star is filled when it is already on your watchlist, otherwise, it is an empty star.

Add symbol directly from the watchlist

  1. Open your watchlist (see View your watchlist)
  2. Tap the + (plus) button
  3. Enter the share symbol or company name
  4. Tap search
  5. Tap the symbol in the search results displayed, No companies will be displayed when no shares match your search term from step 3.

Remove symbol directly from the watchlist

  1. Open your watchlist (see View your watchlist)
  2. Locate the row containing the share symbol you would like to remove and swipe it to the left
  3. Tap the delete icon to remove the symbol, or swipe right to cancel

View your portfolio and share holdings

  1. Open the navigational drawer (see Navigation Drawer)
  2. Select Quotes
  3. Tap the Portfolio tab button displayed on the tab bar
  4. See Portfolio reference page for an overview

View your transaction history

  1. Open the navigational drawer (see Navigation Drawer)
  2. Select Transactions
  3. See Transactions reference page for an overview

Buy and sell shares

Buy and sell using an order ticket

  1. To buy or sell using an order ticket you first need to look up a quote (see Lookup a stock quote)
  2. Tap the trade button to display the order ticket.
  3. Select Buy or Sell, change the symbol of required, and enter an order quantity amount
  4. An estimate of the total order value and brokerage fees will be calculated using the latest market price available, tap the Place Order button to send your order.
  5. See Order ticket reference page for an overview on this screen

Sell all your shares from the positions screen

  1. Open your portfolio (see View your portfolio and share holdings)
  2. Locate the row containing the share symbol you would like to sell and swipe it to the left
  3. Tap the Close to place a market order to close your position, or swipe right to cancel

View the leaderboard

  1. Open the navigational drawer (see Navigation Drawer)
  2. Select Leaderboard
  3. See Leaderboard reference page for an overview

Navigation drawer

The navigation drawer slides in from the left and contains the navigation destinations for the app.

  1. The current user signed is displayed
  2. The navigation drawer
  3. Outside the navigation drawer

Open the navigation drawer

The drawer can be opened in multiple ways:

  • By swiping - Drag the drawer open by swiping in from the left edge. This works on all screens, except for the Sign In and Signup screens.
  • Using the menu button - For screens that have an app bar (aka action bar), a menu button may be available on the left side. If an Up button is displayed instead you can continue to tap that button until it is replaced by a menu button.

Close the navigation drawer

The drawer will close automatically if you select a destination from those listed. If you change your mind and now want to stay on the current page you can close the drawer by tapping outside of the drawer.

App bar

The app bar is a special kind of toolbar that contains a navigation button on the left, a title in the middle, and actions on the right. Less used actions may be accessible from an overflow menu to the right of the actions.

  1. The navigation (menu or up button) location
  2. The title location
  3. The actions location

Navigation button

The navigation button will either be an Up button (showing an arrow pointing left, or up), or a menu button. The Up button navigation you to a previously viewed page. The menu button will open the navigation drawer.

Title text

The title text will normally show the title of the section you are currently viewing, but it may also show the app name or title of the contents you are viewing.

Action buttons

Related actions for the page you are viewing can be accessed or performed using these buttons. Sometimes these buttons will be displayed in an overflow menu.

  •   Up button (yes it is a back arrow), goes up the navigation stack
  •   Filter list
  •   Open the navigation drawer
  •   Contains additional actions, opens the overflow menu
  •   Refresh
  •   Search

Quote

Summary section

The summary section displays a last trade price, change, percent change, and a price line chart.

  1. Share symbol
  2. Company name
  3. Industry of the company
  4. Order button
  5. Star button to add or remove the share from the watchlist
  6. Last trade price
  7. Direction arrow; up if the day change is positive, down if negative, or equal if no change recorded
  8. Days change in price and percent
  9. Chart date range selection toolbar
  10. View fullscreen price chart
  11. Inline price chart display
  12. Last time the quotes data was retrieved from the server

Key stats section

The key statistics section displays financial ratios, dividends, and other values based on price history.

News section

The news section displays recent news headlines related to the currently selected share.

  1. Time when the news article was published
  2. Link to article, opens in system browser
  3. Article headline
  4. Article teaser

Portfolio

The portfolio screen displays your current share holdings, your profit and loss, the total value of your portfolio and the free cash you have available for new trades. You can also close positions from this screen.

  1. Switch between portfolio and watchlist
  2. Quantity of shares held
  3. Share symbol
  4. Average price of shares held
  5. Total cost of shares held
  6. Share last trade price
  7. Value of shares held at last trade price
  8. Profit or loss in cash and percent
  9. Total share and cash values for portfolio
  10. Last time the data was received from the server

Watchlist

The watchlist displays last price and day change values. You can customise the symbols shown in the list.

  1. Share symbol
  2. Company name
  3. Day change direction arrow
  4. Last trade price
  5. Day change as price and percent
  6. Add button
  7. Last time the data was received from the server

Fullscreen chart

The fullscreen chart screen displays a line or candlestick chart displaying a shares prices history over a specified range. To view a hourly chart select the 1MO range.

  1. Summary bar shows; symbol, interval, last interval OHLC values
  2. Price axis (y-axis)
  3. Last interval close price
  4. Date axis (x-axis)
  5. Close price series
  6. Watermark, shows; symbol, interval
  7. Chart date range selection buttons
  8. Chart type; candle or line
  9. Candlestick price series

Price prediction chart

The price prediction chart displays the price history of a share and the predicted price of the share based on a machine learning.

Order ticket

The order ticket allows buying and selling of shares at current market prices.

  1. Buy or sell order selection
  2. Share symbol to buy or sell
  3. Order quantity
  4. Cash available in trading account
  5. Share last trade price
  6. Estimated order value
  7. Estimated brokerage cost (commissions)
  8. Estimated total order cost
  9. Place the order, sends order to server without additional confirmation

Leaderboard

The leaderboard shows the top percentage gainers, the players who are most profitable.

Transactions

The transactions screen lists your share buying and selling history, commisions, and other virtual money transactions. You can filter the list to only show transactions between two dates, and to only show buy and sell (trade) transactions.

  1. Local time of the transaction
  2. Transaction memo
  3. Debit or credit amount
  4. Running balance
  5. Date section, local date of the transaction

Profile

The profile screen allows you to view and edit your email and display name. Your display name is shown on the Leaderboard.

Sign Out

The sign out confirmation screen. Select Yes to sign out, No to return to the screen you were last viewing.

About

The about screen shows some information about the app.
